Tavatron watched as Cyber Claw sunk down and bared her teeth, she knew what 
was to come next. One didn't bare their teeth at another without intending 
some sort of threat. Tavatron could see Cyber Claw tense with each step 
Dinobot took towards her. He wasn't exactly helping the situation either, 
but she could understand where he was coming from. This 'bot was trying to 
steal Dinobot's very identity, something that was his and his alone.

Tavatron watched in horror as Cyber Claw lunged at Dinobot, striking the 
first blow. This was about to erupt into an all out battle, the last thing 
anybody needed. In one fluid motion Tavatron unsheathed her drill sword and 
pressed it to the back of Cyber Claw's neck. She took a sideways glance at 
Dinobot, as if to say 'don't attack her'. She then turned back to the raptor 
standing before her, pressing the tip of her blade a little harder against 
Cyber Claw's neck, but not hard enough to draw mech-fluid:

"Now, please, no one wants to fight. We know you are not who you claim to 
be, and we will NOT harm you."

Tavatron gazed over at Dinobot, though she was speaking to Cyber Claw she 
wanted to be sure he heard her. Tavatron knew the chance was slim to none 
that he would let Cyber Claw's attack go unpunished, but one could always 
hope:

"Please, just transform so we may solve this dispute peacefully."
